@Swift 

You are welcome in the very prestigious club of people who had to do double, triple, and quadruple takes on that one! 

It amused me to see a window, not widow, clue in this puzzle after that!

@HeathieJ 

I think "tilted window" should now be NYT Xworders slang for a clue that is easily misread.  Joining "natick" and "emu".  I think others have been coined along the way.

It is truly astonishing how so many people can misread something in exactly the same way.

